@startuml per-path-auth-enforcement
' One weak handshake setting on :8443, plus a per-path client-auth decision tree in HTTP middleware.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/llm/listener-tls.md
!include _style.puml

start
:**TLS handshake on :8443**\n**ClientAuth = tls.VerifyClientCertIfGiven**\n(permissive on purpose: a caller with no client\ncert must still complete the handshake);

:Route by **path family** (HTTP middleware);

if (path family?) then (**LLM proxy**)

  :/v1/messages\n/v1/chat/completions\n/v1/completions\n+ adapter-registered\nprovider paths;

  if (Client cert present?) then (yes)
    :**Mode 1: mTLS**\nNamespace from the SAN.\nSAN shape + label\ncount enforced.\n(Bearer header, if\nalso present, is\nignored: mTLS wins.);
  else (no)
    if (Authorization: Bearer present?) then (no)
      :**401 Unauthorized**\nneither auth\nmaterial present;
      stop
    else (yes)
      :**Mode 2: bearer**\nPod-ownership\nprecheck **first**,\nthen TokenReview;
    endif
  endif

elseif (path family?) then (**agent-report**)

  :/v1/agent/heartbeat,\n/v1/task/complete;

  if (Client cert present?) then (no)
    :**401 Unauthorized**\n**regardless of any**\n**bearer header**\n(mTLS-only: no\nbearer fallback);
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif
  :Admitted on an Agent\n**or** AgentTask SAN;
  :**Handler-level**\n**caller-type split**\nheartbeat: **Agent** only\ntask-complete:\n**AgentTask** only\nthe other kind:\n**403 Forbidden**;

else (**controller-only**)

  :/v1/activity,\n/v1/channels/health;

  if (Client cert present?) then (no)
    :**401 Unauthorized**;
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif
  if (SAN matches the\ncontroller Service DNS?) then (no)
    :**403 Forbidden**;
    stop
  else (yes)
  endif
  :Authorized as the controller;
endif

:Proceed to the handler;
stop

legend bottom
  **The inversion is the point.** One socket serves three auth regimes, and a single
  tls.Config.ClientAuth value cannot express path-conditional requirements.
  **RequireAndVerifyClientCert** would lock out gateway-only-tier callers: their handshake
  would fail before the path router ever ran. **NoClientCert** would silently downgrade the
  mTLS tier: a cert would be presented but never verified. So the handshake is deliberately
  weak and the per-path tree above carries the whole enforcement burden. A routing bug here
  would let agent-cert holders reach controller-only paths.
endlegend
@enduml
